This paper deals with motion planning for hybrid systems, which involves both continuous and discrete dynamics. The paper specifically focuses on bounded-rate multi-mode systems, which are a type of hybrid system that can switch among a finite set of modes. This makes the paper most likely to belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves algorithms and decision problems, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-categories. The paper also deals with robotics and motion planning, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves some theoretical analysis and complexity results, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
